6:["$","article",null,{"className":"pt-36 pb-32 px-6","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-8","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"pill-tag text-xs font-semibold px-3 py-1 rounded-full","children":"Etsy SEO"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs","style":{"color":"#404060"},"children":"April 2025 · 7 min read"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"font-black leading-tight mb-6","style":{"fontSize":"clamp(30px, 4.5vw, 46px)","lineHeight":1.15},"children":"7 Etsy SEO Tips That Actually Work in 2025"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg mb-12 leading-relaxed","style":{"color":"#8080a0"},"children":"Etsy's search algorithm has evolved significantly. The vague advice circulating in Facebook groups — \"use all 13 tags!\" and \"add keywords to your description!\" — isn't wrong, it's just incomplete. Here's what actually moves the needle."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"tip-block","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-start gap-4 mb-4","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"tip-number","children":"1"}],["$","h2",null,{"style":{"marginTop":0,"marginBottom":0},"children":"Lead Your Title with the Exact Phrase Buyers Type"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Etsy's algorithm weights the ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"first 40 characters of your title"}]," more heavily than anything that follows. This is not speculation — Etsy's own seller handbook says the beginning of your title carries the most SEO weight."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The mistake most sellers make: starting with their brand name or a descriptor instead of a keyword. \"Sunshine Studio — Personalized Oak Cutting Board\" buries the real keyword. \"Personalized Oak Cutting Board — Wedding Gift, Engraved\" leads with what buyers search."}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Before writing your title, ask yourself: ",["$","em",null,{"children":"what would someone type into Etsy's search bar at the exact moment they are ready to buy this?"}]," That phrase belongs at the front."]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"tip-block","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-start gap-4 mb-4","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"tip-number","children":"2"}],["$","h2",null,{"style":{"marginTop":0,"marginBottom":0},"children":"Use All 13 Tags — But Make Each One a Phrase, Not a Word"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Etsy allows 13 tags and each can be up to 20 characters. Single-word tags like \"candle\" or \"gift\" are nearly useless — the competition is enormous and the buyer intent is zero. Long-tail phrases like \"lavender candle gift for her\" or \"stress relief birthday gift\" are what actually convert."}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Each tag should represent a ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"distinct search query a different type of buyer might use"}],". Think about the occasions (Mother's Day, wedding, housewarming), the recipient (gift for mom, gift for new homeowner), the benefits (stress relief, aromatherapy, clean burn), and the material or style (soy wax, hand-poured, minimalist)."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"A good rule of thumb: if your tag is one word, it's probably too broad. If it reads like something a real human would type, it's probably right."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"tip-block","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-start gap-4 mb-4","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"tip-number","children":"3"}],["$","h2",null,{"style":{"marginTop":0,"marginBottom":0},"children":"Match Your Tags to Your Title Keywords"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Etsy explicitly states that when your title and tags contain ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"matching phrases"}],", it sends a stronger relevancy signal to the algorithm. This is called \"reinforcement\" — your title and tags are corroborating each other."]}],"$Lf","$L10"]}],"$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18"]}],"$L19"]}]}]
